<span id="freeTextContainer12556342631740249327">What a treat this book was to read! I thoroughly enjoyed it -- the kids were great, the villain and his heinous plot were quite terrifying, and the plot clipped right along. My one small reservation is that somehow I find I am in no rush to read the sequel -- yet this might have simply to do with the fact that the story did clearly end (unlike, say, <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/2767052.The_Hunger_Games' title='The Hunger Games by Suzanne Collins' rel='nofollow noopener'>THE HUNGER GAMES</a>). But basically, I&apos;d recommend MYSTERIOUS BENEDICT SOCIETY to anyone. I plan to give my copy to a bright 11-year old girl I know. </span>
  <span id="freeText12556342631740249327" style="display:none">What a treat this book was to read! I thoroughly enjoyed it -- the kids were great, the villain and his heinous plot were quite terrifying, and the plot clipped right along. My one small reservation is that somehow I find I am in no rush to read the sequel -- yet this might have simply to do with the fact that the story did clearly end (unlike, say, <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/2767052.The_Hunger_Games" title="The Hunger Games by Suzanne Collins" rel="nofollow noopener">THE HUNGER GAMES</a>). But basically, I'd recommend MYSTERIOUS BENEDICT SOCIETY to anyone. I plan to give my copy to a bright 11-year old girl I know. </span>
